      <div>

<p>We're introducing a trial demand responsive bus service to determine if it has the potential to complement current public transport services and reduce car dependency in the London Borough of Sutton.&nbsp;</p>
</div>
 <div class="clearfix">
    <div class="image-box campaign-graphic left-float">
    
        <img src="/cdn/static/cms/images/go-sutton-logo.gif" alt="go sutton logo" />
    </div>
    <p>The trial service is called <a href="http://www.gosutton.co.uk">GoSutton</a> and is run in collaboration with <a href="https://www.viavan.com/">ViaVan</a> and <a href="https://www.go-ahead.com/en/index.html">Go-Ahead</a>. Services started on Tuesday 28 May 2019 and will run for 12 months. This trial is in line with the commitments in the Mayor's Transport Strategy. Its objectives include finding out if the service can support the shift away from car travel and offer a service that is accessible and easy to use.</p> 
</div>
 
