<h3>How it works</h3>

<p>GoSutton takes multiple passengers heading in the same direction and books them into a shared vehicle. The service operates from 'corner to corner', so there are no fixed routes or bus stops. We'll pick you up and drop you off within 200m of your requested destination. This helps us ensure that even with multiple pick-ups, there are no lengthy detours.</p>

<ul>
	<li>The service can be booked by customers aged 13 and over</li>
	<li>Journeys can be booked by phone or through&nbsp;the GoSutton&nbsp;app available on the <a href="https://www.apple.com/uk/ios/app-store/">App Store&nbsp;</a>and <a href="https://play.google.com/store">Google Play</a></li>
	<li>Services will operate between 06:30 and 21:30, Monday to Sunday except Christmas Day</li>
	<li>Journeys cost &pound;3.50</li>
	<li>Oyster cards and contactless are not accepted</li>
	<li>Freedom Pass holders and members of the English National Concessionary Travel Scheme can travel free on the service</li>
	<li>Buses are fully accessible</li>
</ul>

<p>Find out more about the service on the <a href="http://www.gosutton.co.uk">GoSutton website</a>.</p>
